WEBVTT

00:00.285 --> 00:04.240
We use "under" to talk about a position that is below something.

00:05.265 --> 00:06.149
For example:

00:06.671 --> 00:08.489
The table is under the lights.

00:08.995 --> 00:10.980
The chairs are under the table.

00:11.693 --> 00:14.500
The coffee maker and sink are under the shelves.

00:16.028 --> 00:20.065
We use "above" when we locate someone or something in a higher position.

00:20.872 --> 00:21.553
For example:

00:21.751 --> 00:24.385
The calculator and pen are above the paper.

00:25.006 --> 00:26.761
The plant is above the table.

00:27.569 --> 00:30.337
The pencil can and glass of water are above the tray.

